### Helpers Module

Pure utility functions with no side effects.

#### Object Utilities

**`objectKeys(obj)`**
```typescript
function objectKeys<T extends object>(obj: T): Extract<keyof T, string>[]
```
Type-safe Object.keys.

**`objectEntries(obj)`**
```typescript
function objectEntries<T extends object>(obj: T): ObjectEntries<T>
```
Type-safe Object.entries with proper tuple types.

**`objectValues(obj)`**
```typescript
function objectValues<T extends object>(obj: T): T[keyof T][]
```
Type-safe Object.values.

**`isObject(value)`**
```typescript
function isObject(value: unknown): value is Record<string, unknown>
```
Checks if value is a plain object.

**`assertObject(value, message?)`**
```typescript
function assertObject(
  value: unknown,
  message?: string
): asserts value is Record<string, unknown>
```
Asserts value is an object, throws otherwise.

**`getProperty(obj, path, allowFalsy?)`**
```typescript
function getProperty<T, P extends Paths<T>>(
  obj: T,
  path: P,
  allowFalsy?: boolean
): PathType<T, P>
```
Deep property access with dot notation. Throws on falsy values unless `allowFalsy` is true.

```typescript
const user = { address: { street: '123 Main' } };
const street = getProperty(user, 'address.street'); // '123 Main'
const zip = getProperty(user, 'address.zip', true); // undefined (allowed)
```

**`setProperty(obj, path, value)`**
```typescript
function setProperty<T extends object, P extends Paths<T>>(
  obj: T,
  path: P,
  value: PathType<T, P>
): T
```
Deep property setter.

**`keyBy(arr, key, onDuplicate?)`**
```typescript
function keyBy<T>(
  arr: T[],
  key: keyof T | ((item: T) => string),
  onDuplicate?: (key: string, value: T) => void
): Record<string, T>
```
Convert array to keyed object.

```typescript
const users = [{ id: 1, name: 'John' }, { id: 2, name: 'Jane' }];
const byId = keyBy(users, 'id');
// { '1': { id: 1, name: 'John' }, '2': { id: 2, name: 'Jane' } }
```

**`reduceObject(obj, reducer)`**
```typescript
function reduceObject<R extends object, O extends object>(
  obj: O,
  reducer: (entry: [keyof O, O[keyof O]]) => Partial<R>
): R
```
O(N) object reduction using mutation (performant).

**`deepFreeze(obj)`**
```typescript
function deepFreeze<T extends object>(obj: T): Readonly<T>
```
Recursively freeze an object.

**`requireAll(record)`**
```typescript
function requireAll<T>(record: Partial<T>): T
```
Assert all values in record are non-falsy.

**`objectHasOwnProperty(obj, key)`**
```typescript
function objectHasOwnProperty<T>(obj: T, key: unknown): key is keyof T
```
Type-safe hasOwnProperty check.

**`flatRecordRecords(prefix, record)`**
```typescript
function flatRecordRecords<Prefix extends string, Record>(
  prefix: Prefix,
  record: Record
): FlatRecordRecords<Prefix, Record>
```
Flatten nested records with CamelCase keys.

```typescript
flatRecordRecords('App', { user: { load: fn } });
// { AppUserLoad: fn }
```

#### Error Utilities

**`invariant(value, message?, parent?)`**
```typescript
function invariant(
  value: unknown,
  message?: string | ((typeName: string) => string),
  parent?: Function
): asserts value
```
Assert value is truthy.

```typescript
invariant(user.id, 'User ID is required');
invariant(data, typeName => `Expected data, got ${typeName}`);
```

**`InvariantError`**
```typescript
class InvariantError extends Error {
  static logSensitiveData: boolean;
  constructor(
    message: string | { message: string; stack?: string },
    parentFn: Function,
    extraInfo?: any
  )
}
```
Custom error with stack trace manipulation.

**`tryCatch(handler, parent?)`**
```typescript
function tryCatch<T>(
  handler: () => T,
  parent?: Function
): readonly [Error, never] | readonly [never, T]
```
Safe error handling returning tuple.

```typescript
const [error, result] = tryCatch(() => JSON.parse(data));
if (error) {
  console.error('Parse failed:', error.message);
} else {
  console.log('Parsed:', result);
}
```

**`moveStackTrace(errorOrFn, newStack)`**
```typescript
function moveStackTrace<T>(error: Error, newStack: Function): Error
function moveStackTrace<T>(fn: () => T, newStack: Function): T
```
Relocate error stack trace or wrap function with stack manipulation.

**`createErrorList(prefix?)`**
```typescript
function createErrorList(prefix?: string): {
  add(message: string): void;
  check(): void;
  getError(): never;
}
```
Collect multiple errors and throw single combined error.

```typescript
const errors = createErrorList('Validation failed: ');
if (!name) errors.add('name is required');
if (!email) errors.add('email is required');
errors.check(); // Throws if any errors were added
```

**`isErrorLike(value)` / `assertErrorLike(value)`**
```typescript
function isErrorLike(value: unknown): value is { message: string; stack: string }
function assertErrorLike(value: unknown): asserts value is ErrorLike
```
Error type guards.

**`captureStackTrace(error, constructor?)`**
```typescript
function captureStackTrace(error: Error, constructor?: Function): void
```
Cross-platform (Node.js/Bun) stack trace capture.

#### String Utilities

**`isString(value)`**
```typescript
function isString(value: unknown): value is string
```
String type guard.

**`assertString(value, options?)`**
```typescript
function assertString(
  value: unknown,
  options?: { notEmpty?: boolean; message?: string }
): asserts value is string
```
Assert value is string, optionally non-empty.

```typescript
assertString(name);
assertString(name, { notEmpty: true, message: 'Name is required' });
```

**`capitalize(value)`**
```typescript
function capitalize<T extends string>(value: T): Capitalize<T>
```
Capitalize first letter.

```typescript
capitalize('hello'); // 'Hello'
```

#### Time Utilities

**`ms(timeString)`**
```typescript
function ms(timeString: MSTimeString): number
```
Convert time string to milliseconds.

| Unit | Description | Example |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `y` | Years | `'1y'` |
| `mo` / `mon` / `months` | Months | `'6mo'` |
| `w` | Weeks | `'2w'` |
| `d` | Days | `'7d'` |
| `h` | Hours | `'24h'` |
| `m` / `min` | Minutes | `'30m'` |
| `s` | Seconds | `'60s'` |
| `ms` | Milliseconds | `'500ms'` |

```typescript
ms('1s');   // 1000
ms('5m');   // 300000
ms('1h');   // 3600000
ms('1d');   // 86400000
ms(500);    // 500 (number passthrough)
```

**`delay(time?)`**
```typescript
function delay(time?: number): Promise<void>
```
Promise-based delay (default 500ms).

```typescript
await delay(1000); // Wait 1 second
await delay();     // Wait 500ms
```

#### Date Utilities

**`formatDate(date, pattern, options?)`**
```typescript
function formatDate(
  date: Date | string | number,
  pattern: string,
  options?: { locale?: Locale }
): string
```
Format dates using date-fns patterns.

```typescript
formatDate(new Date(), 'yyyy-MM-dd');     // '2025-12-28'
formatDate(new Date(), 'MMMM dd, yyyy');  // 'December 28, 2025'
formatDate('2025-01-15', 'MMM dd');       // 'Jan 15'
```

**`setDefaultDateLocale(locale)` / `getDefaultDateLocale()`**
```typescript
function setDefaultDateLocale(locale: Locale | null): void
function getDefaultDateLocale(): Locale | null
```
Set/get global date locale.

```typescript
import { ptBR } from 'date-fns/locale';
setDefaultDateLocale(ptBR);
formatDate(new Date(), 'MMMM'); // 'dezembro'
```

#### Development Utilities

**`devLog(message, ...args)`**
```typescript
function devLog(message: string | Error, ...args: any[]): void
```
Log only in development mode. Does NOT throw - safe to use in catch blocks.

**`devAssert(error)`**
```typescript
function devAssert(error: Error): void
```
Throw only in development mode. Silent in production.

**`setLogMode(mode)`**
```typescript
function setLogMode(mode: 'production' | 'development'): void
```
Set logging mode (auto-detected from `NODE_ENV`).

```typescript
import { devLog, devAssert, setLogMode } from '@zazcart/toolkit';

// Log in development only
devLog('Debug info:', someData);
devLog(new Error('Something went wrong')); // Logs error, doesn't throw

// Throw in development only
devAssert(new Error('Invalid state')); // Throws in dev, silent in prod

// Override auto-detection
setLogMode('development');
```

#### Other Utilities

**`createProxy(thunk, target?)`**
```typescript
function createProxy<T extends object>(thunk: () => T, target?: object): T
```
Lazy initialization proxy. Thunk executed on first property access.

```typescript
const config = createProxy(() => {
  console.log('Initializing...');
  return loadExpensiveConfig();
});
// 'Initializing...' only prints when config is first accessed
```

**`maskData(value)`**
```typescript
function maskData(value: any): object
```
Replace leaf values with type names for safe logging.

```typescript
maskData({ id: 123, email: 'john@example.com' });
// { id: 'Number', email: 'String' }
```

**`getTypeOf(value)`**
```typescript
function getTypeOf(value: any): string
```
Human-readable type name.

```typescript
getTypeOf(null);           // 'Null'
getTypeOf(NaN);            // 'NaN'
getTypeOf(new Date());     // 'Date'
getTypeOf(new Date('x'));  // 'Invalid Date'
getTypeOf({});             // 'Object'
getTypeOf([]);             // 'Array'
```

**`EMPTY`**
```typescript
const EMPTY: unique symbol
```
Unique sentinel value to distinguish from `undefined`/`null`.

